author: @CrashTheGooner
text: Nice Explanation Krish Thank you keep up the good work, I have a small explanation regarding a VM vs container that you explain @11:54. VM's are full blown OS and are used to host containers as well. Ideally you are assigning <Host Port> : <Container Port> and thereby allowing the traffic from container to Host using prescribed ports. Also in case of a VM its the localhost and containers run only user defined processes and there by needing you to connect docker containers host's IP address to access its process.
